      <hedline>
        <hl1>Back of the Envelope</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>New report shows that venture capital firms invested $25.5 billion in 2005; graph shows amount invested and number of deals from 1995 to 2006 (S)1</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Venture capital has been climbing back from the bursting of the technology bubble. Last year, American venture capital firms invested $25.5 billion in 3,416 deals, up 12 percent from $22.8 billion in 2005, according to a new report.</p>
      </block>
